### Module 9 — Security Essentials

@base = http://localhost:3000

# ─── Inspect security headers ─────────────────────────────

### GET with -I to see headers only (use curl for this one)
GET {{base}}/headers-check

###
# curl -I http://localhost:3000/headers-check
# Look for: X-Content-Type-Options, X-Frame-Options, Content-Security-Policy


# ─── Rate limiting ────────────────────────────────────────

### Hit this repeatedly — watch RateLimit-Remaining count down
GET {{base}}/rate-limit-check

### Auth limit (10 per 15min)
POST {{base}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{ "email": "test@example.com", "password": "test" }


# ─── Mass assignment protection ───────────────────────────

### Try to inject isAdmin — it should be stripped by Zod
POST {{base}}/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "James",
  "email": "james@example.com",
  "isAdmin": true,
  "role": "superuser"
}

### Validation error
POST {{base}}/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "J",
  "email": "not-an-email"
}
